The goal of this crate is to provide Rust bindings to the Web APIs and to allow
 a high degree of interoperability between Rust and JavaScript.

defs.name: IEvent
defs.docs:
The `IEvent` interface represents any event which takes place in the DOM; some
 are user-generated (such as mouse or keyboard events), while others are
 generated by APIs (such as events that indicate an animation has finished
 running, a video has been paused, and so forth). There are many types of event,
 some of which use other interfaces based on the main `IEvent` interface. `IEvent`
 itself contains the properties and methods which are common to all events.

defs.name: ChangeEvent
defs.docs:
The `ChangeEvent` is fired for input, select, and textarea
 elements when a change to the element's value is committed
 by the user. Unlike the input event, the change event is not
 necessarily fired for each change to an element's value.

A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IElement](trait.IElement.html)
 interface.

defs.name: IHtmlElement
defs.docs: The `IHtmlElement` interface represents any HTML element.

defs.name: focus
defs.docs: The `IHtmlElement` interface represents any HTML element.

defs.name: blur
defs.docs: The `IHtmlElement` interface represents any HTML element.

defs.name: dataset
defs.docs: The `IHtmlElement` interface represents any HTML element.

defs.name: HtmlElement
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IHtmlElement](trait.IHtmlElement.html)
 interface.

defs.name: ImageElement
defs.docs: The HTML image element is used to manipulate the layout and presentation of `` elements.

defs.name: InputElement
defs.docs:
The HTML input element is used to create interactive controls
 for web-based forms in order to accept data from the user.

defs.name: IWindowOrWorker
defs.docs:
The `IWindowOrWorker` mixin describes several features common to
 the `Window` and the global scope of web workers.

defs.name: set_timeout
defs.docs:
The `IWindowOrWorker` mixin describes several features common to
 the `Window` and the global scope of web workers.

defs.name: TokenList
defs.docs: The `TokenList` represents a set of space-separated tokens.

defs.name: TextNode
defs.docs: The `TextNode` represents the textual content of an [IElement](trait.IElement.html)

defs.name: NodeList
defs.docs:
`NodeList` objects are collections of nodes such as those returned by properties
 such as [INode::child_nodes](trait.INode.html#method.child_nodes) and the
 [Document::query_selector_all](struct.Document.html#method.query_selector_all) method.

defs.name: StringMap
defs.docs: Used by the `dataset` HTML attribute to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.

defs.name: Location
defs.docs:
The `Location` interface represents the location (URL) of the object it
 is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates
 to. Both the [Document](struct.Document.html) and [Window](struct.Window.html)
 interface have such a linked `Location`, accessible via [Document::location](struct.Document.html#method.location)
 and [Window::location](struct.Window.html#method.location) respectively.

defs.name: Storage
defs.docs:
The `Storage` interface of the Web Storage API provides access to
 the session storage or local storage for a particular domain.

defs.name: IBlob
defs.docs:
A blob object represents a file-like object of immutable, raw data.
 Blobs represent data that isn't necessarily in a JavaScript-native format.

defs.name: len
defs.docs:
A blob object represents a file-like object of immutable, raw data.
 Blobs represent data that isn't necessarily in a JavaScript-native format.

defs.name: mime
defs.docs:
A blob object represents a file-like object of immutable, raw data.
 Blobs represent data that isn't necessarily in a JavaScript-native format.

defs.name: Blob
defs.docs:
A reference to a JavaScript object which implements the [IBlob](trait.IBlob.html)
 interface.

defs.name: File
defs.docs:
The File interface provides information about files and allows JavaScript
 in a web page to access their content.

defs.name: FileList
FileReader
defs.docs:
The FileReader object lets web applications asynchronously read the contents of files
 (or raw data buffers) stored on the user's computer, using [File](struct.File.html)
 or [Blob](struct.Blob.html) objects to specify the file or data to read.

defs.name: ReaderResult
defs.docs: The result of a read operation performed with a [FileReader](struct.File.html).

defs.name: ReadyState
defs.docs: A number indicating the state of the `FileReader`.

defs.name: ArrayBuffer
defs.docs:
The `ArrayBuffer` object is used to represent a generic, fixed-length raw binary data buffer.
 You cannot directly manipulate the contents of an ArrayBuffer; instead, you create an [TypedArray](struct.TypedArray.html)
 to do it.

defs.name: TypedArray
defs.docs: JavaScript typed arrays are array-like objects and provide a mechanism for accessing raw binary data.

defs.name: ConversionError
defs.docs:
A structure denoting a conversion error encountered during
 serialization or deserialization.

defs.name: Serde
defs.docs:
A newtype which makes it possible to pass a value which implements
 Serde's `Serializable` into the [js!](macro.js.html) macro.

defs.name: serde
defs.docs: A module with serde-related APIs.

defs.name: web
defs.docs: A module with bindings to the Web APIs.

defs.name: error
defs.docs: A module containing error types.

defs.name: html_element
defs.docs: A module containing HTML DOM elements.

defs.name: event
defs.docs: A module containing JavaScript DOM events.

defs.name: unstable
defs.docs:
A module containing stable counterparts to currently
 unstable Rust features.
